<br>
1. Pick up raids<br>
<br>
They are a great idea. I have been doing pick up raids a lot in the last three months (since leaving my old guild) and the result has always been at the same time fun and instructive. So yes, I like the idea and yes, I think opening it to non Scarab members really makes sense. The way I have done it in the past is usually the following : I do a pick up with friends list and friends guilds, and then could do a sentence on the Scarab chat list to see of folk want to join.<br>
<br>
I personnally (but this is just my opinion of course) love the fact that in Scarab, there is an open attitude to &quot;folk from the outside&quot; and I find it a very refreshing attitude to what you have in some gulids. So I do feel a bit uneasy about, for example, doing a pick up raid in a Scarab way and not being able to invite friends who are not members of Scarab.<br>
<br>
In such pick up raids, I actually personnally would not consider the looting system and points as applicable : these are spur of the moment decisions, unofficial, open to all people in Norrath and friends outside Scarab should be able to attend : as such, attributing points and using the points system for loot is, in my opinion not necessary. <br>
<br>
Of course, I am more a social player than one intent on loot, but promoting diversity is something I feel a lot about and what I like a lot with Scarab : why restict it to Scarab only ?<br>
<br>
2. Scarab raids<br>
<br>
This does not prevent normal Scarab raids in any way ; in that way there are Official Scarab Raids, with advertisement, points, restriction on attendance, loot rules, and then there are Spontaneous Pick Up raids which can have other loot rules, no points and so on. Which leads me to 3.<br>
<br>
