<br>
The one aspect where there was some disagreement was how open the pickup raid should be. If we had 50 plus members of SCARAB on line at peak times and SCARAB was mostly 55 plus players I could see a restriction to SCARAB only working. I have tried on three occasions to get a pickup raid started and the most response I have had is from 3 players. With that number to go against Gorenaire, you would be leading a Kamikaze raid, with certain failure. As a family team we have helped several people on the 55 level mobs, where a small pickup group is much better with a lot less organising, minimum down time and more fun in achieving something. My original suggestion was to enable us to hit the bigger 60 plus rare spawn mobs on the server and for that we need 15 to 20 plus players, especially if we have a 50 plus raid policy.<br>
<br>
I take Silds point about bad pickup raids being a disaster. I for one was scammed on the last server on quite a few Vox and Naggy raids, where all the loot was suddenly allocated to the leaders or their friends. On one Vox raid I had my worst experience on Everquest, the raid started at 10.30pm and we finally recovered all the corpses at 9.15am the following morning.<br>
<br>
This leads on to rules I am not a person who likes too many rules, and one reason I have found most Everquest guilds not to my liking is the clique that forms with officer only forums (only he can lead raids, the officers council will decide who is worthy of No Drop loot etc). I do not like all that crap and one reason I am committed to SCARAB is the complete openness we have. However if we are to develop pickup raids and make them popular again under the SCARAB banner. There is a need for rules, this is to ensure fair distribution of loot and have a reference so people know the rules when they join a Scarab pickup group. There is also the need to maintain the reputation and credibility of SCARAB on the server; otherwise the hard work of building SCARAB up will soon be lost with a few disastrous raids.<br>
<br>
This is my idea of a minimal rules format, please feel free to give your own opinions and reduce or extend the basis of the rules, but this at least can be a starting point.<br>
<br>
RULES FOR SCARAB PICKUP RAIDS<br>
<br>
1) Only full members of SCARAB can organise and lead a pickup raid organised under the SCARAB banner and rules.<br>
2) The raid will be open to who ever the Leader chooses to invite, but all SCARAB members in game at the time of the announcement will have the right to attend.<br>
3) The Leader will give a clear estimate of the time required, ideal minimum level and the degree of risk.<br>
4) Only special items relating to Quests can be reserved by the Leader the rest will be considered random loot.<br>
5) The basis for rolling on the loot will be NEED BEFORE GREED.<br>
6) A player can win only one piece of loot per raid. (A player with more than one account cannot keep rolling with an alternate character if they have already won a piece of equipment/spell).<br>
7) No raid will be started by a Leader unless they can offer all participants a minimum 90% res and if in a high risk area have organised some method of corpse retrieval.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
I feel that is a simple basis to work on and hope to get your feedback, so we can all increase the fun content of the game.<br>
<br>
Many Thanks<br>
